description.narrative:
The Strategic Sector Cooperation on Food aims to improve the Kenyan food control system in the entire value chain, involving compliance of food business operators and risk assessment for the benefit of human health and increased export potentials by:

-	Strengthening the national food safety control system in Kenya; 
-	Improving the feed and dairy regulation and food safety control in the dairy sector; 
-	Raising awareness on how to control pesticide residues in horticulture and improve plant health raised
-	Securing efficient use of laboratories and reliability of results.
